The articles of incorporation of a savings and loan association shall set forth:
The name of the association;
The county in which the association's first principal place of business is to be located;
A precise and accurate statement of the purpose or purposes for which the association is organized, as well as a statement that it is organized in compliance with State law;
The term for which the association is to exist, which may be perpetual;
The name, occupation, citizenship, place of residence, and post office address of each incorporator;
The name, occupation, citizenship, place of residence, and post office address of each of the first directors; and
If the association is a capital stock association, provisions for the issuance of capital stock.

The proposed bylaws of the association shall provide for:
The dates of regular meetings of shareholders, if any;
The notice of the regular meetings to be given;
The qualification of voters and the manner of voting;
The manner of calling special meetings;
The number of members that constitute a quorum; and
The date of the annual meeting;
The number of directors and their qualifications, other than those specified in this title;
The terms of office of the directors which may not be less than 1 year or more than 3 years;
If the terms of office are more than 1 year, the method of division into classes for the purpose of electing, as nearly as may be, an equal number of directors each year; and
The removal or suspension of directors;
The meetings of the board of directors; and
The powers and duties of the board of directors;
The officers;
The manner of election of the officers;
The terms of office, duties, and compensation of the officers; and
The bonds required of officers;
The classes of shares that may be issued;
The issuance of shares, whether issued in series or otherwise;
The times when shares may be issued; and
The matured value of shares;
The manner in which evidence of share ownership shall be issued to members;
The time and manner of apportioning, crediting, and paying dividends;
The conditions upon which shares may be transferred, matured, withdrawn, retired, or suspended and forfeited; and
The manner and conditions under which the bylaws may be altered or amended.
